The paper presents a practical algorithm for computing the margin of victory in Instant Runoff Voting (IRV), which is a voting scheme used in elections. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the category of Computer Science and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DS) as it deals with algorithms and computation. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and search techniques, which are commonly studied in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the correctness of election outcomes, which is related to Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Game Theory (cs.GT).
